Study Population Summary

July 22, 2025

Study population definiton: patients enrolled for at least 180 days in Kaiser data with an index dx coming from encounter types AV, ED, IP, or IS that had >= 70% of visits in [180,0] window with temp reading.

## 1 LO                 7
## 2 OE               221
## 3 RO                 2
## 4 VC               175

In the 180-days prior to the index diagnosis, 2678 patients of the total 3420 patients had at least one healthcare visit prior to the index for any reason. Break down of visits that occurred prior to index:

There were 742 patients whose first visit occurred on the index date. Of these patients whose first visit occurred on the index date, 742 had temperature reading on the index visit as well, with 112 (15.09%) patients having a fever based on a temp >= 100F.

There were 2466 patients that had a healthcare visit prior to the change-point of 14 days. However, there were only 1716 patients that had a healthcare visit during the delay window (i.e.,[-14, 0)). There were a total of 3378 visit days during the delay window among the 1716 patients, of which 86.68% of the visit days had a temperature reading. Among visit days with a temperature, 6.22% had a fever reading of >=100F.
